  "prompt": "I did really bad on my 1st term of 11th (cbse).If I pull myself together and do really well on the other 2 terms can I still get above 95% at the end?",
  "response": "It's definitely possible to improve your overall score if you perform well in the remaining terms, but it will depend on a few factors:\n\n1. **Weightage of Each Term:** Check how much each term contributes to your final grade. If the first term has a lower weightage compared to the subsequent terms, you have a better chance to significantly impact your final score by performing well in the second and third terms.\n\n2. **Improvement Strategy:** Analyze where you went wrong in the first term. Identify the subjects or topics that need more focus and work on them. Create a study plan that prioritizes these areas and includes regular revisions and practice tests.\n\n3. **Consistent Effort:** Consistency is key. Make sure you dedicate regular time to studying and stick to your study schedule. Avoid last-minute cramming and ensure you understand the concepts thoroughly.\n\n4. **Help and Resources:** If necessary, seek additional help from teachers, tutors, or online resources. Joining study groups or online forums can also provide support and help clarify difficult topics.\n\n5. **Exam Techniques:** Practice previous years' question papers and work on your exam techniques, like time management and answering strategies. This will help you improve your performance in the actual exams.\n\nIf you follow these steps and remain determined, you should be able to significantly improve your scores in the following terms and have a strong chance of achieving an overall percentage of above 95%.",
